# Frontend Next.js Practices

- This version has breaking changes: APIs, conventions, and file structure may differ from training data.
- Read the relevant guide in `frontend/node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before writing or refactoring code.
- Heed deprecation notices and avoid introducing legacy patterns.
- Prefer server-first patterns in App Router unless client state is required.
- Keep `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars as the only browser-exposed environment variables.
- Ensure `npm --prefix frontend run lint`, `typecheck`, and `build` pass for UI changes.
